CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 20, 1965, pg. 19 reads: " Alpha Council Honors "Queens" - A reception held recently at Greater Pittsburgh Lodge 115, sponsored by Alpha Council No. 1, IBPOE of W. honored two "queens." Left to right, seated: Dts. Eva Saunders, Eula Williams, queen; Arlene Nichols,Clara Randolph, queen; Marian Charles, runner-up; Gloria Bassett and Elsie Wimbush.  Standing: Dts. Catherine Johnson, chairman; Maxine Davis, Hester R. Thomas, state president; Carl Dickerson, speaker and Chief Antler; Madie Jordan, Loyal Daughter Ruler; Barbara Cuff, Hattie McClain, Daughter Ruler, and Dorothy Lowry, chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Elk daughters, seated, from left: Eva Saunders, Eula Williams, Arlene Nichols, Clara Randolph, Marian Charles, Gloria Bassett, and Elsie Wimbush; standing: Catherine Johnson, Maxine Davis, Hester R. Thomas, Carl Dickerson, Madie Jordan, Barbara Cuff, Hattie McClain, and Dorothy Lowry, gathered behind table in Greater Pittsburgh Lodge 115 for reception
